The Denali National Park Improvement Act ( ) is a bill that was introduced into the United States Senate during the 113th United States Congress .
If enacted , the bill would do four main things .
First , it would allow the United States Department of the Interior to " issue permits for microhydroelectric projects in the Kantishna Hills area of the Denali National Park and Preserve in Alaska . "
Second , the bill would authorize the Department of the Interior and a company called Doyon Tourism , Inc. to exchange some land in the area .
Third , the bill would authorize the National Park Service ( NPS ) to " issue permits to construct a natural gas pipeline in the Denali National Park . "
Finally , the bill would rename the existing Talkeetna Ranger Station the Walter Harper Talkeetna Ranger Station .
